pages.general_notes_verbatim:
GENERAL NOTES:
1. DESIGN AND CONSTRUCTION OF ALL WORK ON THIS PROJECT SHALL CONFORM TO LATEST EDITION OF THE ONTARIO BUILDING CODE
2. DRAWINGS ARE NOT TO BE SCALED.
3. CONTRACTOR SHALL MAKE ALLOWANCE IN PROVIDING TEMPORARY BRACING AND SHORING DURING CONSTRUCTION TO RESIST THE DESIGN LOADS.
4. ALL ROOF TRUSSES SHALL BE DESIGNED, FABRICATED AND ERECTED IN CONFORMANCE TO CSA S307.
5. ALL STEEL SHALL BE DESIGNED, FABRICATED AND ERECTED IN CONFORMANCE TO CSA S16.
6. ALL CONCRETE SHALL BE DESIGNED, FABRICATED AND ERECTED IN CONFORMANCE TO CSA A23.3.
pages.page_overview_summary: This sheet contains general structural notes and a detailed truss bracing diagram. It outlines design loads and construction standards, ensuring compliance with the Ontario Building Code. The notes provide essential guidelines for the structural integrity and safety of the building, covering aspects from material specifications to construction practices.
